</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="110" pageNumber="506" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="110.[161,1370,1235,2129]" pageId="110" pageNumber="506">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[163,511,1900,1933]" pageId="110" pageNumber="506">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. The Caspian White-toothed Shrew is a common or occasionally abundant species in the Hirkan National Park (Azerbaijan) in the northern part of its range and, together with mice of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kaup" authorityYear="1829" box="[345,477,2026,2051]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Apodemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="110" pageNumber="506" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Apodemus</taxonomicName>
, dominates in communities of small mammals.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
